The paper deals with the complexity of the maximum coverage problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also presents a fixed-parameter tractable approximation scheme, which is a common topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of greedy algorithms and local search, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
